cy_in_corpus":344,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":false},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n7027","n7028","n7029"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AD%D9%8E%D8%AA%D9%8E%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n7027","headword_ar":"حَتِّ","root":"Ht","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(indecl., with kesr for its termination, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A cry by which birds are chidden."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n7028","headword_ar":"حَتٌّ","root":"Ht","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HutaAt","text_ar":"حُتَات"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Dead;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as though strewn upon the ground, in fragments;] applied to locusts ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaraAd","text_ar":"جَرَاد"},{"kind":"text","text":"): pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHotaAtN","text_ar":"اَحْتَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) its only pl. (MF.) [Hence, app.,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tarakuwhumo Hat~FA bat~FA","text_ar":"تَرَكُوهُمْ حَتًّا بَتًّا"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hat~FA fat~FA","text_ar":"حَتًّا فَتًّا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They destroyed them."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Dates"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tamor","text_ar":"تَمْر"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not sticking together."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, * TA.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Huv~N","text_ar":"حُثٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b4-  (tropical:)  A"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fleet,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"swift,"},{"kind":"text","text":"horse; (S, A;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as though he scraped the ground;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"light in pace, and wide in step:"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl. as above: (S:) or a"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fleet,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"swift, and excellent"},{"kind":"text","text":"horse; (K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that runs swiftly and much,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that furrows the ground much with his feet:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"generous and high-bred"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kariymN EatiyqN","text_ar":"كَرِيمٌ عَتِيقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. as applied to a horse]): (K:) and a"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fleet,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"swift,"},{"kind":"text","text":"camel: (K:) a"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quick-paced and light-paced"},{"kind":"text","text":"camel; as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HatoHatN","text_ar":"حَتْحَتٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a male ostrich."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) The Hudhalee says, (S,) namely, El-Aalam, (TA,)"},{"kind":"page_break","n":509},{"kind":"quote","text":"ElY Hat~i AlburaAyapi zamoxariY~i Also\n                      \n                     \n                        sawaAEidi Zal~a fiY $aroYK TiwaAli"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA:) he likens himself, says As, in his running and fleeing, to a male ostrich, as is shown by what precedes this verse: (S:) by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ht~ AlbrAyp","text_ar":"حتّ البراية"},{"kind":"text","text":"is said to be meant"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hat~K Einoda AlburaAyapi","text_ar":"حَتٍّ عِنْدَ البُرَايَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e. (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fleet,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"swift, when emaciated by journeying;"},{"kind":"text","text":"the subst."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"brAyp","text_ar":"براية"},{"kind":"text","text":"being said to be put for the inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baroY","text_ar":"بَرْى"},{"kind":"text","text":": (A, * L:) some of the Basrees say that the poet means a camel; but As disapproves of this, because to that which he here describes he has before applied the epithet"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hijaf~","text_ar":"هِجَفّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": ISd says that in his opinion he likens his horse or his camel to a male ostrich, because of the epithet"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hjf~","text_ar":"هجفّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", preceding, and because neither the horse nor the camel eats the colocynth, but this plant is cropped by ostriches;"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$rY","text_ar":"شرى"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning the colocynth: IJ says that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$rY","text_ar":"شرى"},{"kind":"text","text":"here signifies a tree of which bows are made; and the poet means that if the trees thus called are tall, they conceal him, and he is the more lonesome, or sad; and that if they were short, his eye would range freely, and he would be pleased, and would run gently. (L.)       -A2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hat~aY","text_ar":"حَتَّى"},{"kind":"text","text":", near the end of the paragraph."}],"source_refs":["S","TA","K"]},{"entry_id":"n7029","headword_ar":"حُتٌّ","root":"Ht","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", applied to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"swiyq","text_ar":"سوِيق"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"malotuwtN","text_ar":"مَلْتُوتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Moistened,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stirred about, with water,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (K.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Huv~N","text_ar":"حُثٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":[]}]}}